The course consists of Spanish phonetics and text analysis. The text analysis is focused on developing reading skills. The phonetics course consists of two parts: practical pronunciation exercises and the theoretical part which includes the description of Spanish phonetical system (the characteristics of vowels and consonants) as well as an introduction to phonetic transcription.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to acquire Spanish pronunciation and to learn to understand simple written texts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course the students:
TEXT ANALYSIS:
1) can read and understand simple written texts in Spanish;
2) has acquired basic strategies for written text comprehension.
PHONETICS:
1) know the rules of Spanish pronunciation and orthography;
2) are acquainted with the basics of phonetics and phonetic transcription.
